The single-bit mode records whether the byte have been executed.
The byte mode includes a 6-bit hit counter and 2-bit byte type. Byte type records if the byte was an instruction heading, body, or tailing, or overlapped. An overlapped byte is the byte interpreted as differing instructions. If any byte of the current instruction overlaps with another one then the entire instruction is considered overlapped.
The word mode increases the hit counter to 14 bits.
There is an instruction counter counting number of instructions stepped, but that's currently unused. It will be recorded in future modes.
