. I'm afraid part of this issue won't be added soon. Code folding feature
saves each range in a tree. It does not allow overlapping ranges to be
folded. The code folding line is drawn only if the code segment is added in
the tree. Therefore, you either have to register the range of the entire
function in the tree, thus do not allow people fold two functions, or keep
it as what it behaves today.
As for selecting the first instruction hides the checkbox. Folding of the
entire selection is always prioritised. If the selection has only one
instruction then the checkbox is hidden because folding a single
instruction is a silly operation.
. It is also common in Visual Studio code. Visual Studio tend to put function
