whereas NtCreateUserProcess will give
NTSTATUS NtProcessStartup(PPEB Peb);
This could be worked around: start the process, allocate and write a small loader stub in it, make the stub call DllMain with the module base (obtainable from the PEB), FwdReason = DLL_PROCESS_ATTACH, and NULL for the reserved parameter since no one uses it anyway, and finally use NtSetContextThread to change the entry point of the thread before resuming it.
