The problem is that x32dbg.exe has two handles to the debuggee process (one received from CreateProcess by TitanEngine, one received from the kernel in the debug loop when CREATE_PROCESS_DEBUG_EVENT occurs). If you close x32dbg while the debugee is running, the process is terminated before SafeSymCleanup is called with the first handle.
