IMO an entry breakpoint for an image with no entry is nonsensical. Surely there must be an entry before there can be an entry breakpoint? Changing it to the system BP is basically changing the meaning of 'entry breakpoint' to 'system breakpoint' for 0.01% of images. I think it would confuse people more that the behaviour is inconsistent than that it would help anyone. If I want a system breakpoint, I just check the checkbox for that in the options.
The 'no-op' fix is also consistent with how the other breakpoint settings work. If I have 'TLS callbacks' checked, but the image doesn't have TLS callbacks, does x64dbg set a BP on the call to LdrpCallTlsInitializers as a replacement instead? No, that wouldn't make any sense.. Ahh, I see. Yes, in that case setting the entry breakpoint 'as late as possible' would have been a good fix. Shame it doesn't work then :/
