void* -> ULONG_PTR is always well-defined AFAIK since ULONG_PTR is defined to be an unsigned integral of pointer size. The overflow check is also well-defined because it uses unsigned overflow, not signed overflow which is indeed UB.. Following up - I checked the PE spec and didn't find any mention of a size restriction for either the import or export directories. Even corkami's files don't have something that test this (surprisingly). So I think that 'assume the worst' applies here, i.e. 2^32.
